dmin/config/regional/i18n/strings?render=overlay','default','When translating user defined strings that have a text format associated, translators will be able to edit the text before it is filtered which may be a security risk for some filters. An obvious example is when using the PHP filter but other filters may also be dangerous.','','7.43'),(1426,'/es/admin/config/regional/i18n/strings?render=overlay','default','As a general rule <strong>do not allow any filtered text to be translated unless the translators already have access to that text format</strong>. However if you are doing all your translations through this site\'s translation UI or the Localization client, and never importing translations for other textgroups than <i>default</i>, filter access will be checked for translators on every translation page.','','7.43'),(1427,'/es/admin/config/regional/i18n/strings?render=overlay','default','<strong>Important:</strong> After disallowing some text format, use the <a href=\"@refresh-strings\">refresh strings</a> page so forbidden strings are deleted and not allowed anymore for translators.','','7.43'),(1428,'/es/admin/config/regional/i18n/select?render=overlay','default','Content to filter by language','','7.43'),(1429,'/es/admin/config/regional/i18n/select?render=overlay','default','Content selection mode','','7.43'),(1430,'/es/admin/config/regional/i18n/select?render=overlay','default','Enable for specific pages','','7.43'),(1431,'/es/admin/config/regional/i18n/select?render=overlay','default','All pages except those listed','','7.43'),(1432,'/es/admin/config/regional/i18n/select?render=overlay','default','Only the listed pages','','7.43'),(1433,'/es/admin/config/regional/language/configure','default','Session language detection configuration','','7.43'),(1434,'/es/admin/config/regional/language/configure','default','URL language detection configuration','','7.43'),(1435,'/es/admin/config/regional/language/configure','default','User interface text','','7.43'),